Print parameter table to console, flextable, latex, or (latex) pdf file

Source: R/printParameterTable.R
printParameterTable.Rd

Print parameter table to console, flextable, latex, or (latex) pdf file

Usage

printParameterTable(
  pars,
  engine = "kable",
  format,
  footnotes = NULL,
  script = NULL,
  file.mod,
  include,
  include.pattern,
  drop,
  drop.pattern,
  include.fix,
  caption
)

Arguments

pars

A parameter table as generated by `NMwork::createParameterTable()`.

include

A character vector of symbol values to include. All else will be dropped.

include.pattern

A regular expression run on the `symbol` column. What matches will be kept.

drop

A character vector of symbol values to drop. All else will be kept.

drop.pattern

A regular expression run on the `symbol` column. What matches will be dropped.

include.fix

Either a logical or "NotZero". `TRUE` means fixed parameters are not filtered out, `FALSE` means they are filtered out, "NotZero" means they are only kept if not equal to zero.

Examples

file.mod <- system.file("nonmem/xgxr134.mod",package="NMwork")
pars <- createParameterTable(file.lst=file.mod,
                  args.ParsText=list(format="%idx; %symbol ; %label [%unit] ; %trans",
                                     format.sigma="%symbol - %label "))
#> Column(s) added: panel
#> Warning: diag(V) had non-positive or NA entries; the non-finite result may be dubious
printParameterTable(pars=pars,format="R")
